text: Hmm.
Trying to find a direction for any of the new Bant-chantress commanders by reading any and all forum posts. Mtgsalvation is full of complaints about Tuvasa, and it’s hilarious.
Tuvasa probably plays a bit like Bruna
I am super happy with Estrid. I couldn't have designed a better walker to go with the deck I have built
I threw in a Chain Veil to go info and win with Helix Pinnacle
Truly living the best life.
Tuvasa seems to be their catch-all commander. She facilitated anything you want, and since a lot of people really wanted minimum an enchantress in the Zone I think she’s great.

But yea, complaints I’ve seen:
“She’s so boring/simple.”
“She has no interaction with Merfolk.”
“Once per turn is lame because they’re making you play enchantments on curve instead of enchantment storm.”
“She doesn’t protect herself.”
What a wonderful place.
Tuvasa is to enchantress what Sahili is to the artifact deck. Both are for first time people playing the archetype

One of my buddies doesn’t get why I (or anyone) would like Tuvasa. I look at Estrid and see a combo commander and I look at Kestia and see awkward non-Voltron Voltron (wide not tall). Tuvasa is simple and classic, so I like it
I don't get how bant enchantment players can dislike Estrid or Tuvasa. Do the same broken enchantment crap you've always been doing but hey you now have a Commander that synergizes with it!
Maybe boring, I guess, but people are acting like they don't like them at all

It’s strange. I like them all. Kestia is stylish, and she’s the one I’ve tried figuring out.
Her Bestow cost is just rough though.
Tuvasa having a Helm of the Gods stapled on is fun.
They're all so different, it's almost like they wanted them to feel unique!
I'm not surprised you could ask 3 different people and get 3 different favorites from pretty much all the decks this year
Definitely. Legends are a great mix of obvious, weird, build around, and unique.
So apparently someone sucker punched Jeremy Hambly at GenCon?
And he's playing up the sob story?
… Good?
Am I allowed to say that?
I'll allow it
Oh, good!
